</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="AA6DFFF1C784B7E4DD8A55715209004A" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">
<taxonomicName id="DDB59FFA9A0930292FED1BCA562F1430" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel &amp; Oviedo" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia povedae" order="Myrtales" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="povedae">
<emphasis id="340239D3771E80C2B20543308E6F655B" italics="true" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">Conostegia povedae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very narrow endemic easy to recognize because of its rusty indument, sessile leaves with attenuate leaf bases and which are strongly plinerved, and sessile flowers in clusters that when in bud have a fused calyx that ruptures irregularly. In their evidently yellow anthers, exserted styles, and geniculate filaments, 
<taxonomicName id="FA9759CDE0BAB61F0DC4BC446159D734" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel &amp; Oviedo" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia povedae" order="Myrtales" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="povedae">
<emphasis id="238A3B089DA221CF795FFFD7FEA4CF99" italics="true" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">Conostegia povedae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows the typical floral morphology present in section 
<taxonomicName id="5A87F57B7324C1B79C6D83AC4B89B1F1" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Geniculatae">
<emphasis id="197DFE8FB1DC8A7100802D8A85406225" italics="true" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">Geniculatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
